The base syntax of CSS is built upon 3 elements: selector, property and value:
selector{property: value;}

E.G.:

h1{color: green; font-family: comic-sans;}

Contextualized E.G.:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  
<head>
    <!-- Style on h1 elements -->
    <style>
        h1 {
            color: green;
            text-align: center;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <h1>GeeksforGeeks</h1>
</body>
  
</html>
